      <processinfo id="aspace_4906fc77380c6c2d0f17b87cb2cf907b">
         <head>Processing Information</head>
         <p>Yale University records are arranged and described at the accession level by the creating office. The University Archives creates collection level descriptive records, but typically does no further arrangement and description at the accession level.</p>  
      </processinfo>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_da0841a231c0066936ea9962ff3670b6">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The records consist of memoranda, correspondence, reports, and financial records documenting the activities and operations of the vice-president for development and alumni affairs. The files of Charles E. Lord, John A. Wilkinson, and Terry Holcombe detail the activities of major administrative figures. Materials related to the Yale Alumni Fund are also included.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_bbb64ba7049d90a4907ea6f66c62a5e2">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The records are arranged by accession.</p>  
      </arrangement>
